title: Executive Order 5510-Power-Site Restoration No. 456
content: So much of the orders of May 26, 1909, creating Temporary Power-Site Withdrawal No. 5, and of July 2, 1910, creating Power-Site Reserve No. 5, as affects the following described lands is hereby revoked:
T. 33 N., R. 108 W., sec. 34, SW. ¼ NE. ¼, SW. ¼ SE. ¼.
citation: Herbert Hoover, Executive Order 5510-Power-Site Restoration No. 456 Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/372995
